<TITLE> RMG workers to march to PMO if unpaid </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 13 (bdnews24.com)Jatiya Garment Workers Federation on Sunday said it would organise a march toward the prime minister's office if the salaries, back pay and allowances of six closed readymade garment factories were not settled by Tuesday. "Six garment factories have closed without around 1,500 employees receiving salaries and allowances, many of them were laid off illegally," JGWF president Amirul Haque Amin told reporters after a protest outside the Directorate of Labour's office, Sram Bhaban, on Rajuk Avenue. The JGWF president and around 100 garment workers 'besieged' the chief factory inspector's office, under the Directorate of Labour, demanding settlement of all workers dues ahead of Eid. Amin asked the inspector to explain which law allowed the six factories to close without first clearing what was owed to their employees. "If no-one listens to the laid-off workers, who can guarantee they will coolly see the situation through?" he questioned. The JGWF chief warned factory owners would not be permitted to enjoy the Eid festivities in peace if their former employees were not paid. After a half-hour siege, protest leaders submitted a letter to the chief factory inspector outlining their demands. b
